<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id6b0454b4-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s22"><num value="22">§ 22.</num><heading> Bayou Meto, Arkansas</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Bayou Meto, in the State of Arkansas, is declared to be a nonnavigable stream within the meaning of the Constitution and laws of the United States.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id6b0454b5-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">(<ref href="/us/act/1917-08-08/ch49/s16">Aug. 8, 1917, ch. 49, § 16</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/40/268">40 Stat. 268</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
